# Primitives — reusable design-system components

Primitives live in `src/renderer/components/primitives/`. They are imported by every screen. Treat them like a tiny published library — small, predictable, documented.

## Folder structure (per primitive)

```
primitives/<Name>/
  <Name>.tsx     ← component + Props type
  <Name>.css     ← optional, only if the primitive needs its own CSS rules
  index.ts       ← re-export
```

`index.ts` is just `export { default } from './<Name>';` plus any type re-exports. Screens import from the folder, not the file.

## Props contract

- `type Props = {…}` above the component, never inline.
- Required props first, optional with defaults destructured (`{ size = 'md' }`).
- Variants and sizes as **union types**, not boolean flags.
- Pass-through ARIA props (`aria-label`, `aria-describedby`) where the primitive doesn't always carry visible text.
- Event handlers named (`onClick`, `onToggle`); avoid leaking implementation-specific event types.

## Variants cap

A primitive has at most **4 variants** (e.g. `primary | secondary | ghost | danger`). If you need more, you have two components, not one — split it.

## State coverage

Every interactive primitive handles, visually:

1. default
2. hover
3. focus-visible (visible ring using `--border-strong`)
4. active / pressed
5. disabled (uses `--ink-disabled`, `--surface-disabled` — not `opacity`)
6. loading (if it triggers async)

Non-interactive primitives (`Pill`, `Kbd`, `Divider`) just handle default + optional emphasis.

## Tokens only

Primitives reference only semantic tokens (`var(--ink-primary)`, `var(--surface-raised)`). Never:

- Raw hex / rgb / hsl
- Primitive layer tokens (`--sand-50`, `--ink-50`)
- Hard-coded font/spacing/radius values off the scale

## No external layout

A primitive does NOT impose margins on its outer edge. The parent positions. Internal padding is fine.

```tsx
// Bad — primitive imposes layout
<button style={{ marginTop: 12 }}>…</button>

// Good — parent positions
<div style={{ marginTop: 12 }}><Button>…</Button></div>
```

## Composition

Primitives compose other primitives. Example: `IconButton` uses `Icon`. `Card` may render any children. Composite primitives (`Card`, `EmptyState`, `Toast`) are allowed and live in the same folder.

## Documentation

Every primitive has an entry in `design/components.md`. The entry includes:

- Location
- Purpose (one line)
- Props summary
- Variants
- States covered
- Tokens used
- Status: `mvp | tokenized | primitive | ready`
- Used by (which components/screens consume it)

When you add or change a primitive's API, update the doc in the same change.

## Story (when Ladle exists)

Once Ladle is installed (Phase 2g), every primitive gets `<Name>.stories.tsx` next to its source — one story per variant, plus an "all states" story.

## Anti-patterns (auto-reject)

| Bad | Why |
|-----|-----|
| Primitive owns its margin/position | Mixes layout and component concerns |
| `className` prop that overrides internal style | Breaks encapsulation — add a real `tone`/`variant`/`size` instead |
| `disabled` styled with `opacity: 0.5` | Multiplies against background; token-driven disabled is required |
| Boolean flags that mean variant (`isPrimary`, `isDanger`) | Variant union is clearer and exhaustive |
| Children + label both for the same content | Pick one API; document it |
| 200+ line component file | Split. A primitive should be ≤150 lines |

Invoke `needle-build-component` to create or extract a primitive; it walks the full contract.
